Bolivia Fashion Week<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://boliviafashionweek.com/|title=Bolivia Fashion Week - La Semana de la Moda de Bolivia|website=Bolivia Fashion Week|language=es-ES|access-date=2016-09-26}}</ref> took place for the first time in [[Bolivia]] on April 5 to 8, 2016 in the Bolivian city of [[Cochabamba]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lostiempos.com/click/moda/20160406/bolivia-fashion-week-inicia-primera-version-cochabamba/|title=Bolivia Fashion Week inicia la primera versión en Cochabamba|website=Los Tiempos|language=es-ES}}</ref>. [https://www.facebook.com/boliviafw/ Bolivia Fashion Week] is an annual event that showcases both emerging designers, brands and cultural fashion innovators. The presence of [[Agatha Ruiz de la Prada]] from Spain, and other world designers in the [http://www.agatharuizdelaprada.com/fitting-bolivia-fashion-week-cochabamba/ Bolivia Fashion Week 2016 event], highlighted the goal of the fashion week to connect talented local designers with the global fashion industry, as stated by Bolivia Fashion Week's founder, Pamela Alarcon.

