[[File:BMW M3 -4.jpg|200px|thumb|left|Image of a racing car with lead room]] {{Css Image Crop | Image = Leonardo_da_Vinci_(ur_Svenska_Familj-Journalen).png | bSize = 300 | cWidth = 130 | cHeight = 150 | oLeft = 80 | oTop = 10 | Location = right | Description = Without lead room }} {{Css Image Crop | Image = Leonardo_da_Vinci_(ur_Svenska_Familj-Journalen).png | bSize = 300 | cWidth = 150 | cHeight = 150 | oLeft = 80 | oTop = 10 | Location = right | Description = With lead room }} In [[photography]], [[filmography]] and other visual arts, '''lead room''', or sometimes '''nose room''', is the space in front, and in the direction of, moving or stationary subjects.<ref name="c2">{{cite web|url=http://www.mapacourse.com/DVpages/leadroom.htm |title=Lead room |publisher=mapacourse.com |access-date=2007-08-09 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929025752/http://www.mapacourse.com/DVpages/leadroom.htm |archivedate=2007-09-29 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title = The Essential Digital Video Handbook: A Comprehensive Guide to Making Videos That Make Money | author = Peter May | publisher = Rotovision | year = 2004 | isbn = 1-59253-024-9 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=zLIAP3_kfBwC&pg=PT170&ots=miv2qQT3U6&dq=photography+%22lead+room%22&ei=RlK7RuWqIIqKoQL3ttXvBQ&sig=uYbX9__o6IwugxjNBxvzAs6dSRw }}</ref> Well-composed shots leave space in the direction the subject is facing or moving.<ref name="c2"/> When the human eye scans a photograph for the first time it will expect to see a bit in front of the subject.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikonians.org/html/resources/guides/composition_101/composition_101_4.html|title=How to Improve Your Photography - Five Easy Composition Tricks|publisher=Tom Boné|access-date=2007-08-09}}</ref>
For example, moving objects such as cars require lead room.<ref name="c1">{{cite web|url=http://www.videomaker.com/article/9231/|title=Framing Good Shots| work=Videomaker Magazine| access-date=2007-08-09}}</ref> If extra space is allowed in front of a moving car, the viewer can see that it has someplace to go; without this visual padding, the car's progress will seem impeded.<ref name="c1"/> {{clear|left}}
